s attributes, use an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygonFeature","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" object."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Alternatively, you can add a polygon overlay directly to a map view using the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapView\/addAnnotation:"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapView\/addOverlay:"},{"text":" method. Configure","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"a polygon overlay’s appearance using","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapViewDelegate\/mapView:strokeColorForShapeAnnotation:"},{"text":" and","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapViewDelegate\/mapView:fillColorForPolygonAnnotation:","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The vertices are automatically connected in the order in which you provide"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"them. You should close the polygon by specifying the same"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CLLocationCoordinate2D"},{"type":"text","text":" as the first and last vertices; otherwise, the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"polygon’s fill may not cover the area you expect it to. To avoid filling the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"space within the shape, give the polygon a transparent fill or use an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolyline","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" object."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A polygon may have one or more interior polygons, or holes, that you specify as"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" objects with the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"+polygonWithCoordinates:count:interiorPolygons:"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"method. For example, if a polygon represents a lake, it could exclude an island"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"within the lake using an interior polygon. Interior polygons may not themselves"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"have interior polygons. To represent a shape that includes a polygon within a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"hole or, more generally, to group multiple polygons together in one shape, use","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"an ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolygon","isActive":true},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolygon","isActive":true},{"text":" object.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To make the polygon straddle the antimeridian, specify some longitudes less"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"than −180 degrees or greater than 180 degrees."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":4,"type":"heading","text":"Related examples","anchor":"Related-examples"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"TODO: Add a polygon annotation, learn how to initialize an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon"},{"type":"text","text":" object from 